 <p>Neotyre Evangelion Warrior of Marr, Neoterre De Kazaire Druid of Tunare Proud followers of The Burning Shield</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uthoricofbrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thoric of Brell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Uber Gimp</span><br>  Posts: 510<br> <font color=#CC9900>(12/11/00 1:31:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/BrianPic_copy.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stats...how important are they to a warrior?</span><hr size=1> Well first things first, I was in the same position you were around 38, and decided to experiment because a friend of mine at the same level had gone ac and was owning mobs i got my butt kicked by.<br>
<br>
So i swapped out equipment for ac, got to 803, and suddenly I was soloing greater kobolds. <br>
<br>
800 is really the first &quot;magic number&quot; for AC, and it reduces the damage you take a LOT, i think the formula they use must create a major breakpoint there. <br>
<br>
On the other hand, stats have had a fairly minor effect on my existance. Str is nice if you are using two handers, but statistically has a small effect on the overall damage i do. It's probably the most important stat for a warrior though. It affects the rate combat skills go up.<br>
<br>
Stamina can be important, because it gives you some extra hp, and that's always nice. <br>
<br>
Dex, well, it does increase my procing and crits somewhat, but it's most important effect seems to be that combat skills go up faster when its high. <br>
<br>
The other stats have next to no effect for me. Agi adds a little ac, but not enough to really help. <br>
<br>
Bottom line, give up the stats, get AC. Eventually as you get better armor, your stats will climb along with the AC. I now am quite satisfactory in both departments.  But do the swap and go fight wherever you are used to fighting, I guarantee you will see a huge difference. <p><A HREF="http://sr.amiga.tm/" TARGET="_new"><IMG ALT="Silent Redemption Member" BORDER=0 SRC="http://home1.gte.net/res007bh/ThoricPSD2_copy.gif"></A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uhethral.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hethral</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/r Where's the corpse.</span><br>  Posts: 556<br> <font color=#CC9900>(12/11/00 2:19:22 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://the.truthbringers.com/Images/Members/HeadShots/HethralHead.jpg BORDER=0></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Stats...how important are they to a warrior?</span><hr size=1> All I know is when the shaman hits the warrior with stat buffs, the monster falls down a little bit faster.<br>
